1.create schema university
2. use university(mentioned database_name)

Data Definition Language

    1.create [NOT NULL]
        syntax:-
            create table table_name(variable variable_datatype(size),
            pincode datatype no_need_to_mention_datatype)

    2.alter - add [syntax:-
                alter table table_name add column column_name datatype(size)]
            - change[syntax:-
                alter  table table_name change old_name new_name datatype(size)]  
            
            - rename 

            - To change only the datatype:- [old_name new_or_old_name datatype(size)]

    3.drop - syntax:- drop table table_name

    4.truncate - syntax:- truncate table table_name

data query language//data manipulation language

    1. select-[where,and,or,not, is null,order by] [syntax:- select (* or column_name)from table_name]

    2. insert- syntax:-insert into table_name values(......)

    3. update -[ set, where, and , or ]
                syntax:- update table_name set metion_name_to_change=value 

    4. delete - syntax:- delete from table_name

DCL- Data Control Language
    1.grant
    2.revoke

TCL- transaction control language
    1.commit
    2.rollback
    3.savepoint


aggregate functions [as]

    1.sum()
            syntax:-
                    select sum(name) from table_name
                    select sum(name)  as name_to_mention from table_name
    2.max()
            syntax:-
                    select max(name) from table_name

    3.min()
            syntax:-
                select min(name) from table_name
    4.avg()
            syntax:-
                select avg(name) from table_name
    5.count()
            syntax:-
                select count(name) from table_name